Scenario: shop-msg response written inside the BC container is readable from the host
  Given the shopsystem-bc-launcher BC is installed
  And a Docker container named "bc-shopsystem-messaging" is running with its mailbox volume mounted
  And an inbox message with work-id "lead-500" exists inside the container
  When shop-msg respond work_done is run inside the container with work-id "lead-500"
  Then running shop-msg read outbox on the host with bc-root pointing to the container's mailbox mount path and work-id "lead-500" exits zero
  And stdout includes message_type "work_done"
